From: EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com [mailto:EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com] On Behalf Of
SnowfireL@...
Sent: Sunday, May 10, 2009 11:38 AM
To: EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com
Subject: Re: [EVP-ITC] File uploading rules








Hi Misty, do you by any chance have a link for, ESNIPS ?



In a message dated 5/10/2009 12:34:25 P.M. Eastern Daylight Time,
bulletbabea@... writes:




Sharing is great. You just have to do it to meet this groups limitations.
Most of us just reply via email and attach the files or use a file sharing
application such as esnips. I wish yahoo allowed more storage space so we
could share unlimited amounts of research. They don&#39;t yet but places like
esnips help us overcome that obstacle. 



Misty

--- On Sun, 5/10/09, SnowfireL@... &lt;SnowfireL@...&gt; wrote:


From: SnowfireL@... &lt;SnowfireL@...&gt;
Subject: Re: [EVP-ITC] File uploading rules
To: EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com
Date: Sunday, May 10, 2009, 12:08 PM

Misty, sorry I deleted my folder, and it&#39;s contents, I guess I thought you
folks wanted people to post in there for study or something, you probably
have enough of your own, sorry, didn&#39;t know. Take care, sf



In a message dated 5/10/2009 12:03:25 P.M. Eastern Daylight Time,
SnowfireL@aol. com writes:



Thanks for sharing your Gold Wave Kristin, I didn&#39;t know how to get the
record button to come up at first, I think &quot;open&quot; has to be highlighted
first?  I don&#39;t know what happened to that little red box thing



In a message dated 5/10/2009 11:49:00 A.M. Eastern Daylight Time,
SnowfireL@aol. com writes:



Hi Kristin, what&#39;s the difference between the two formats?  I don&#39;t have a
clue, I try to do a short 5 minutes session with spirit people last night,
and when I asked, how many here have met God, I got a few people saying,
&quot;me&quot; guess, I ask some pretty dump questions, eh&quot; I counted 5 me&#39;s, and some
that haven&#39;t I guess.



In a message dated 5/10/2009 8:32:14 A.M. Eastern Daylight Time,
ckmorris95@sbcgloba l.net writes:



Snow - In the Goldwave software you can &#39;save as&quot; mp3.  Directly under the
file name in the &quot;Save As&quot; where you name your clip is &quot;File Format&quot;.  Click
on the drop down list arrow and MP3 should be your 2nd choice on the list.
Click MP3 and save.  Your file is now in MP3 format. :-)  I hope this helps.

k


  _____  


